    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a mechanically sound example of the legendary S54-powered platform. The 3.2L high-revving inline-six features individual throttle bodies and has undergone a comprehensive VANOS system refresh and proactive rod bearing replacement to ensure long-term valvetrain integrity. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory limited-slip differential. The chassis has been enhanced with subframe reinforcement plates and Bilstein B16 coilovers, addressing common E46 weak points while sharpening turn-in response. Though it exhibits minor cosmetic wear consistent with an enthusiast-driven vehicle, the mechanical synchronization and compression remain excellent, offering a visceral, analog driving experience.",
      "price": 34800.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 37
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Used car for sale. Good condition. Clean title. Maintenance records available. Runs well. No mechanical issues.",
